CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 19, 1946, pg. 1, reads: "FITTING TRIBUTE - The bier of the late Mrs. Mary Nunn was piled high with many beautiful floral tributes from organizations and friends Tuesday when funeral services were held from the Carron Street Baptist Church. The deceased was one of Pittsburgh's most prominent civic leaders and clubwomen.  She died Saturday, Oct. 12, in Women's Hospital. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Women wearing light colored dresses carrying large funereal floral arrangements out of Carron Street Baptist Church, for funeral of Elizabeth Hopkins Nunn, with pallbearers Chester Washington and Cornelius Jones in background, and Rev. Phillips standing near car and telephone pole
